Third-party glyph licensing
===========================

Most glyphs in `icons/interlux-icons/` are original to this project and ship
under the MIT license above. The exceptions and their original licenses are:

  icons/interlux-icons/system/linux.svg
    Derived from the HashiCorp Design System (https://github.com/hashicorp/design-system).
    Licensed under the Mozilla Public License 2.0 (MPL-2.0). This single file is
    NOT relicensed under MIT; it remains under MPL-2.0 and downstream consumers
    must comply with MPL-2.0 terms for this file. The full MPL-2.0 text is
    available at https://www.mozilla.org/en-US/MPL/2.0/.

The following glyphs were derived from MIT-licensed third-party sources. They
are included under their original MIT license, compatible with this repo's MIT
license:

  icons/interlux-icons/file/cut.svg
  icons/interlux-icons/file/cut-filled.svg
    Derived from Ionicons (https://github.com/ionic-team/ionicons), MIT.

  icons/interlux-icons/system/stats-ram.svg
  icons/interlux-icons/user/accessibility.svg
    Derived from VMware Clarity Assets (https://github.com/vmware/clarity-assets), MIT.

The following glyphs were derived from public-domain sources (sourced via
SVG Repo, https://www.svgrepo.com/) and carry no licensing restrictions:

  icons/interlux-icons/hardware/usb.svg
    Zondicons / Steve Schoger.

  icons/interlux-icons/peripherals/speaker.svg
    Icooon Mono.

  icons/interlux-icons/network/network-ethernet.svg
